&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;At Corvias, you’ll join a team wholeheartedly invested in their work. In return, we offer support intended to strengthen your professional, financial, emotional, and physical wellbeing. Your wellbeing is not just a priority, it’s at the heart of the Corvias employment experience.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Corvias is hosting this job listing on our website for its delivery partner, Vitacorps, to support hiring best-in-class team members who will be strengthening the health, quality of life and readiness of our service members and their families.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who We Are&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Corvias, we’re experts at developing solutions through partnership. Our mission is to be personally committed to solving our partners’ most difficult, systematic challenges by reimagining what is possible and realizing more resilient communities together. We believe a culture of caring, purposeful, diverse and courageous humans who want to make a difference for our partners will help us achieve that mission.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;While the role is remote, we currently only hire selected candidates from the following states: AL, FL, GA, IN, KS, LA, MA, MD, MI, NC, OK, RI, TN, and TX.&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;How You&#39;ll Contribute to the Team:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The EVP, Market Development is a senior executive responsible for driving revenue growth, market expansion, and strategic partnerships primarily but not limited to, the Department of Defense (DoD). This role requires deep experience operating within large, complex enterprises, combined with a strong startup mentality, able to move decisively from strategy to execution while at the same time navigating sophisticated internal and external stakeholder environments. The selected candidate brings demonstrated success selling into the DoD via both traditional and non-traditional means including leading capture strategies, securing contract awards, and scaling DoD‑related revenue while working effectively within enterprise financial, governance, compliance, and decision‑making structures.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Primary Responsibilities Include:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own and lead the DoD market and contracts strategy, including prioritization of services, commands, defense agencies, and related defense organizations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive end‑to‑end business development and capture efforts, including opportunity identification, qualification, capture planning, proposal strategy, and contract execution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Alignment with broader Lobbying efforts for Congressional support and market development&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain senior‑level relationships with DoD officials, prospects, and defense industry partners.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and execute an integrated DoD market strategy aligned with enterprise growth objectives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate complex defense market dynamics into actionable growth priorities and investment decisions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build scalable, repeatable go‑to‑market processes without introducing unnecessary bureaucracy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own revenue growth and performance across assigned portfolios.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead pricing, deal structuring, and margin management for complex contracts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish and manage teaming arrangements, alliances, joint ventures, and partner ecosystems to improve win rates and market access.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Navigate complex corporate and political environments to align Legal, Compliance, Finance, Operations, Product, and Technology teams and joint venture partners around growth priorities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Influence decision‑making across a matrixed organization without relying on formal authority.&lt;/

