&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;At Corvias, you’ll join a team wholeheartedly invested in their work. In return, we offer support intended to strengthen your professional, financial, emotional, and physical wellbeing. Your wellbeing is not just a priority, it’s at the heart of the Corvias employment experience.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who We Are:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At&amp;nbsp;Corvias, we’re experts at developing solutions through partnership. Our mission is to be personally committed to solving our partners’ most difficult, systematic challenges by reimagining what is possible and realizing more resilient communities together. We believe a culture of caring, purposeful, diverse and courageous humans who want to make a difference for our partners will help us achieve that mission.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;How You&#39;ll Contribute to the Team:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Maintenance Supervisor uses advanced knowledge of residential maintenance operations to perform maintenance and repair work and to mentor, train, and direct the work of Maintenance Technicians. This role is accountable for physical operations, preservation, and maintenance of the asset in accordance with SOPs and budget guidelines, ensuring timely completion of work at quality standards. The ability to establish positive, productive working relationships with team members and vendors and to provide residents an exceptional customer experience and quality living environment is at the forefront of this role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Primary Responsibilities Include:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide high quality customer service to all residents by responding to maintenance requests in a timely and professional manner, maintaining a clean workspace in the residents’ home, and performing quality work.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use and follow safety guidelines for tools and equipment and demonstrate on a regular basis operational knowledge of these products.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Plan, organize and direct maintenance personnel, assigning work orders, and make-ready activities including move-in/move-out inspections, as well as 24/7 emergency maintenance schedule.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;As a working supervisor, train and support maintenance technicians, assisting in all maintenance projects, repairs, and Community activities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Process all maintenance orders and maintain adequate inventory control within budgeted guidelines. Forecast potential expenses based upon current operating conditions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist management in the creation and implementation of an effective preventative maintenance plan. Perform regular physical property inspections to ensure proper maintenance and upkeep of all assets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor compliance with Company SOPs and federal and state regulations. Ensure the successful execution of all company safety and environmental policies and procedures.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Solicit and evaluate maintenance contract proposals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Other duties as assigned.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role Specific Requirements Include:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High school education or equivalent level of competence in English and mathematics is required, technical school training strongly preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minimum 6 years’ experience in multi-family housing maintenance or similar industry with 1 year of supervisory or coordination experience required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Certification or comparable experience in four or more trades including: plumbing, electrical, appliance repair, carpentry, masonry, HVAC and building construction; Demonstrable expert level knowledge and use of tools and equipment for specific trades.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;EPA Type I and II certification and basic training for LBP and mold; Demonstrable knowledge of OSHA regulations.&

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;At Corvias, you’ll join a team wholeheartedly invested in their work. In return, we offer support intended to strengthen your professional, financial, emotional, and physical wellbeing. Your wellbeing is not just a priority, it’s at the heart of the Corvias employment experience.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who We Are &amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Corvias, we’re experts at developing solutions through partnership. Our mission is to be personally committed to solving our partners’ most difficult, systematic challenges by reimagining what is possible and realizing more resilient communities together. We believe a culture of caring, purposeful, diverse and courageous humans who want to make a difference for our partners will help us achieve that mission.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;How&amp;nbsp;You’ll&amp;nbsp;Contribute to the Team&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The purpose of this role is to provide superb customer service through timely response and quality maintenance of the physical asset.&amp;nbsp;The maintenance technician performs community maintenance activities under the daily operational supervision of the maintenance supervisor or the lead maintenance technician. This position is also responsible for carrying out general repairs and preventive maintenance to using basic trade skills such as electrical, plumbing, appliance, HVAC, and carpentry work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Primary Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide high quality customer service to all residents by responding to maintenance requests in a timely and professional manner, maintaining a clean work space in the residents’ home&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Responsible for timely completion of all phases of make ready / turnover work, and trouble shooting, according to the turn timeline.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Complete all work tasks in a safe and efficient manner in accordance with company safety standards relaying information that might constitute physical or liability hazard.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use and follow safety guidelines for tools and equipment and demonstrate on a regular basis operational knowledge of these products.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Complete all manner of work order request and fill out appropriate forms such as work orders, daily time sheets, weekly time sheets and any other related documentation in accordance with policy guidelines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in preventative maintenance programs and on-going maintenance and repair of physical assets.&lt;/li&gt;
